Subject: [PATCH] Pin DNA NumPy for reproducible snapshots

Match the dependency set used by the preserved July 8 DNA image that
successfully completed split-container snapshot creation.  Rebuilding from
the unpinned Dockerfile reproduced the older /usr/local/bin/python fault at
VA 0x3120, so do not allow pip to select a different NumPy release.
---
 testcases/testcases/fn_py_dna_visualisation/Dockerfile | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/testcases/testcases/fn_py_dna_visualisation/Dockerfile b/testcases/testcases/fn_py_dna_visualisation/Dockerfile
index 8a10069..27f0ae8 100644
--- a/testcases/testcases/fn_py_dna_visualisation/Dockerfile
+++ b/testcases/testcases/fn_py_dna_visualisation/Dockerfile
@@ -1,5 +1,5 @@
 FROM python:alpine3.17
-RUN pip install minio squiggle==0.3.1
+RUN pip install minio numpy==1.26.4 squiggle==0.3.1
 RUN mkdir func
 COPY /tools/template.py /func/main.py
 COPY prewarm.py /func/prewarm.py
